						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Umāmahēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 11: 982 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that an individual ••••• Veṇkāḍaṉ Siṅgam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Diśaiyāyirat-taiñūṟṟuvaṉ of Tiru[nārāyaṇapuram] endowed some land at Nārāyaṇamukkāṇi, a hamlet, east of Tirunallam after purchase for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple at Tirunallam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> in Veṇ-nāḍu. Among the boundaries, a piece of land which was the <hi rend="italic">śrīdhaṉa</hi> of the wife <hi rend="italic">(śāṇi)</hi> of Bālāśiriyaṉ Dāmōdiraṉ is mentioned.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 280.</p>						

						</summary>
